children.text: This dwelling is in a designated termite zone, and there has not been a 25mm gap provided between the framing members and the masonry to protect from termite infestation that can cause serious damage to the structure.
Part 3.1.4.3 Termite management systems of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that
‘Where a termite management system is required it must comply with AS 3660.1’ .
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3660.1 Termite Management states in clause 3.3.3 Clearance from masonry components, that
‘No portion of timber subfloor members, including bearers, joists or bottom plates, shall be closer than 25mm to any vertical external masonry wall surface, see Figure 3.1(B)’ ;

As the building surveyor has determined that this dwelling is in a designated termite zone, the builder will need to extend the ground clearances to a minimum of 400mm to comply with part 3.4.1.2 of the BCA.
